  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>1. Visual Analog Scoring for Anxiety</measure>
    <time_frame>1 day</time_frame>
    <description>Self reported anxiety score before and after inhalation of aromatherapy. 3 questions about preoperative anxiety are asked and scoring is done based on a 0-10cm scale (0= no anxiety, 10= agonizing anxiety). Cumulative scores for all 3 questions above 5 indicates preoperative anxiety.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>1. Amount of sedation used to achieve Loss of Consciousness</measure>
    <time_frame>Less than 30minutes</time_frame>
    <description>Induction for general anesthesia using Target control Infusion of Propofol 1% (10mg/mL) using the Schnider protocol, administered via a TIVA Agilia infusion pump to achieve a target plasma concentration of 4mcg/ml until loss of consciousness.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
